examples.en: After dinner, we wandered into town
The dog wandered far from home.
She wandered aimlessly about the house.
We wandered around the bazaar looking to buy gifts.
She wandered round all morning, unable to sit still.
They wandered down the street.
He finally wandered in at 3:00 a.m., obviously lit up.
Ana wandered off to get a drink.
The child wandered out of sight.
A cow wandered into the roadway.
His gaze wandered round the room.
He wandered away from the trail and got lost.
They realized they had wandered into a minefield.
I wandered around campus all day in a ruminant mood.
He wandered out again, in a perfect bog of uncertainty.
He wandered around the streets, looking in shop windows.
Mrs Snell's mind wandered and the voices went on and on.
Her smile "wandered" the assistant, he promptly lost grip.
She wandered about in a swoon for several days after receiving the tragic news.
She wandered into the meeting with complete insouciance to the fact that she was late.
